{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2012}} '''Edward George Irving''' (1816–1855) was a Scottish surgeon who served in the [[Royal Navy]]. He was also a collector of plants, and the plant family [[Irvingiaceae]], and genus [[Irvingia]] are named after him.<ref>D. Gledhill. ''The Names of Plants''. Cambridge University Press, 2008.</ref>
==Marriage and Family== He married Lucy Elizabeth Haynes Morrell, second daughter of [[Arthur Fleming Morrell|Arthur]], a [[Royal Navy|British naval]] officer and Elizabeth, on 25 July 1848, at [[Portsea Island#Kingston|Kingston]], [[Portsmouth]], Hampshire.<ref>''The Gentleman's Magazine'', vol. 30, p. 421. July, 1848.</ref>
Their children were Edward Arthur Irving, who became an [[archdeacon]] in Canada, Minnie Irving, and John Henry Irving.
